{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Introduce routine scoliosis screening in primary and secondary schools",
        "additional_details": "My daughter was diagnosed with adolescent idiopathic scoliosis at the age of 12, x-ray showed a severe s-curve that resulted in her having a 14 hr operation. The consultant said if this had been picked up sooner bracing and scroth physio could have been used to stabilise the curve through growth.\r\n \r\nScreening is easy and non-invasive, and many American schools already do this, and many cases are picked up at this point.",
        "background": "To introduce routine screening at the start of the school year for scoliosis in primary and secondary school settings. Adolescent idiopathic scoliosis is a change in the shape of the spine during the child\u2019s growth normally linked to puberty. Early detection can effect the course of the treatment.",
